underlying_goal: To audit a technical report against its underlying codebase and data, identify all inconsistencies, and fix them.
friction_detail: There was confusion about whether newly generated charts contained all models, which was resolved by realizing the user was viewing a stale PDF that needed recompiling. The initial chart generation script also failed due to hardcoded values.
primary_success: Conducted a thorough audit of a technical report against its source data, identifying and fixing numerous critical inconsistencies including a reversed primary finding, incorrect scores, and misleading validation claims.
brief_summary: The user requested an audit of a paper against its code. Claude found major inconsistencies, including a reversed key finding. After the user confirmed, Claude systematically corrected the paper's text, generated new publication-quality charts with specified brand colors, and recompiled the final PDF to resolve all identified issues.
